---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Job Posting Red Flags Checker | Spot Scam Jobs & Bad Employers"
description: "Paste any job posting and instantly identify red flags. Our free tool checks for missing salary info, vague visa promises, contract issues, and other warning signs."
---

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Job Posting Red Flags Checker",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "applicationCategory": "BusinessApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Any",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" }
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How can I tell if a job posting is a scam?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common scam indicators include: requests for upfront payment or fees, vague company descriptions, guaranteed visa approval claims, no interview required, and pressure to send money via wire transfer. Legitimate employers never ask candidates to pay for their own visa processing." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Should a job posting include salary information?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Reputable employers increasingly include salary ranges in job postings. Many countries and jurisdictions now require salary transparency by law. A job posting without any compensation information is a yellow flag—it may indicate below-market pay or an unprofessional hiring process." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is it normal for employers to ask candidates to pay for visa processing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. In virtually all legitimate employment scenarios, the sponsoring employer pays for visa application fees and related legal costs. If a company asks you to pay a processing fee, application fee, or any upfront cost, it is almost certainly a scam." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does 'visa sponsorship may be available' mean?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "This vague phrasing is a warning sign. Companies that genuinely sponsor visas typically state it clearly: 'We offer visa sponsorship' or specify the visa type (EU Blue Card, Skilled Worker visa, etc.). Vague language often means the company hasn't committed to sponsorship or may not follow through." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are commission-only jobs risky for visa holders?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Commission-only roles are risky for visa holders because most work visas require a minimum salary threshold. If your income is entirely commission-based, you may not meet visa requirements, and your income instability could jeopardize your immigration status." }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-white to-indigo-50 dark:from-gray-950 dark:via-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-16 md:py-20">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400">Home</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span>Tools</span>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Red Flags Checker</span>
    </nav>

    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/30 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6">
        <i data-lucide="shield-alert" class="w-8 h-8 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400"></i>
      </div>
